# 📊 Baseline & Endline Evaluation

## Overview

Led the analysis and reporting of baseline and endline studies for the OGI program.

## Challenge

The organization required evidence to determine whether interventions were improving household wellbeing, financial resilience, food security, child protection and social capital.

## My Role

- Supported survey design and review
- Developed data analysis plans
- Conducted statistical analysis
- Produced visualizations and reports
- Interpreted findings for program teams
- Supported dissemination of findings

## Technologies

- R
- Excel
- Power BI
- ODK
- Survey Platforms

## Key Findings

### Savings Participation

Participation in savings groups increased from **48% to 95%**.

### Food Security

Households achieving minimum dietary diversity increased from **18% to 65%**.

### Child Protection

Agreement with physical punishment as a child-rearing practice decreased significantly.

### Social Capital

Communities demonstrated stronger support networks and increased resilience.

